Special variables:
------------------
1. All variables passed to the the script: $@
2. Number of variables: $#
3. Script name: $0
4. Current directory of the user: $HOME
5. User running this script: $USER
6. PID of the script: $$
7. sleep 10 & - command running in the background
   PID of last command in the background: $!

   
Conditions:
-----------
-gt -> greater than
-lt -> less than
-eq -> equal
-ne -> not equal

Install mysql - taken as example to install mysql
possible Conditions:
1. user is running with root access or not
   id command get the user deatils
   id -u -> command to get only user ID
2. if root user proceed to install
3. else show the error to run with the root user